metadata.name: AGORIA {Compend-AI-M} 2016 #16
metadata.description:
Agoria
{Compend-AI-M} #16

Our eyes are constantly tracked but what remains invisible in an art piece? {Compend-AI} is a collection of pieces (movies and stills) which questions the unseen dimensions. 

Where the eye is blind, matter stores memory.

In the intricacies, between each remnant of {Compendia}, an augmented intelligence cruises among the pigments and exposes what the human eye could not see.

An invisible culture is revealed.

The series M of{Compend-AI} is revealing forms and patterns really close to the living. Is there an immanence of the living into the code?

In collaboration with Johan Lescure.

HD file on demand (145mo)
